# LLM JSON Parsing

Claude Haiku often wraps JSON in markdown fences even when told not to. **Never call `json.loads()` directly on raw LLM text.**

## Required pattern

```python
from utils import parse_json

try:
    data = parse_json(response.content[0].text.strip())
except (ValueError, KeyError):
    # return safe fallback — never silently assume success
    ...
```

## Applies to

- `retrieval/router.py` — `_route()`
- `agents/extractor.py` — `extract()`
- `agents/verifier.py` — `verify()`
- `experiments/*` — judge/relevance scoring

## Bad vs good

```python
# ❌ BAD — fails on ```json ... ``` fences, returns empty defaults silently
data = json.loads(text)

# ✅ GOOD
data = parse_json(text)
```

When adding new Haiku/JSON agent calls, always route through `utils.parse_json()`.
